==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[claustrum]]'' "a shut in place," from ''[[claudere]]'' "to close" + Greek ''[[philia]]'' "affection," from ''[[philos]]'' "love."

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪliə|-ɪliə]]

===Noun===
'''claustrophilia'''
# the [[love]] of [[closed]], [[tight]] places

